  "prompt": "How is it possible to open an account in TD Ameritrade for non-US residents?",
  "response": "Opening an account with TD Ameritrade as a non-US resident is possible, but the process may involve specific requirements and documentation. Here are the general steps you might need to follow:\n\n1. **Check Eligibility**: Ensure that you are eligible to open an account with TD Ameritrade. Some countries may have restrictions, so it's important to verify that your country of residence is accepted.\n\n2. **Visit the Website**: Go to the TD Ameritrade website and look for information specifically for non-US residents. They may have a dedicated section outlining the process and requirements.\n\n3. **Choose the Right Account Type**: Decide which type of account you want to open (individual, retirement, etc.), as the requirements may vary based on the account type.\n\n4. **Complete the Application**: Fill out the online application form. Be prepared to provide personal information, including your name, address, date of birth, and financial information.\n\n5. **Provide Identification**: You will likely need to submit identification documents. This may include a passport, driver's license, or other government-issued ID. Additionally, you may need to provide proof of residency, such as a utility bill or bank statement.\n\n6. **Tax Identification Number**: Non-US residents may need to provide a Tax Identification Number (TIN) or a foreign tax identification number, depending on your country of residence.\n\n7. **Fund Your Account**: Once your application is approved, you will need to fund your account. TD Ameritrade typically accepts various funding methods, including wire transfers.\n\n8. **Approval Process**: After submitting your application and documents, there will be an approval process. This may take several days, depending on the completeness of your application and the documentation provided.\n\n9. **Compliance Regulations**: Be aware that TD Ameritrade will comply with international regulations, including anti-money laundering (AML) laws and know your customer (KYC) requirements.\n\n10. **Customer Support**: If you have questions or encounter difficulties, consider reaching out to TD Ameritrade's customer support for assistance tailored to non-US residents.\n\nIt's important to note that policies and procedures may change, so always refer to the official TD Ameritrade website or contact their customer service for the most accurate and up-to-date information.",
